24:40.170 --> 24:42.060
In "Spy car - the revenge",

24:42.390 --> 24:44.790
wheel spikes were a rip roaring success.

24:45.415 --> 24:46.615
Is that enough for you?

24:46.760 --> 24:50.330
So now it's on to secret
agent anecdote number two.

24:51.890 --> 24:53.250
Car mounted guns?

24:53.450 --> 24:55.380
Yes, I have been saying this for years.

24:55.381 --> 24:58.350
The car mounted guns for a spy
car don't make any sense to me.

24:58.560 --> 24:59.710
They are fixed.

24:59.890 --> 25:02.070
You cannot aim them except by driving.

25:02.260 --> 25:04.690
That's got to be a huge
inefficiency for a machine gun.

25:04.890 --> 25:07.560
Well, I have seen some that are
remote-controlled and aim-able, though.

25:07.670 --> 25:08.870
Those are in the minority,
but I have seen them.

25:09.060 --> 25:11.290
So I think we should build
a rig that gives us both.

25:11.480 --> 25:13.740
I chase you with fixed guns on my hood,

25:13.940 --> 25:15.800
and then we can do a second
one where I chase you

25:15.801 --> 25:19.040
with a remote-controlled aim-able
gun mounted to the hood of my car.

25:19.230 --> 25:20.170
Sold.

25:22.710 --> 25:25.810
The hood mounted gun is a
staple for any spy car.

25:26.050 --> 25:28.000
But is it a viable weapon?

25:28.550 --> 25:33.910
Can such a device, fixed or movable,
really guarantee an accurate aim?

25:37.230 --> 25:41.550
Well, to find out, Adam has already
selected his wheels and his weapon.

25:43.810 --> 25:46.140
This is a former police car.

25:46.320 --> 25:51.820
And this is a super high-end ten
round per second paint ball gun.

25:52.200 --> 25:53.820
I'm going to join these two things together

25:54.020 --> 25:56.690
to make two great tastes in one candy bar.

25:57.430 --> 26:01.160
Fabricating the fixed firearm
will be a weld in the park.

26:02.060 --> 26:05.750
But the remote-controlled
firer is a much tougher task.

26:06.930 --> 26:10.200
So for the aim-able gun, I
need to first build a mount

26:10.400 --> 26:12.590
that will let the gun
move in three dimensions,

26:12.780 --> 26:15.550
so I can fire at Jamie's
car wherever it might be.

26:16.430 --> 26:18.170
There's the basics right there.

26:18.390 --> 26:22.020
Up, down, side to side.

26:22.530 --> 26:24.280
Then I'm going to add a joystick system

26:24.450 --> 26:28.120
so that I can control the gun's aim
from inside the car while driving.

26:28.330 --> 26:29.590
That is X-Y control.

26:29.740 --> 26:31.940
Next comes the all important trigger,

26:32.140 --> 26:34.430
so I'll be able to shoot
600 rounds per minute.

26:34.660 --> 26:35.700
I press this.

26:36.360 --> 26:37.490
It ought to fire.

26:40.310 --> 26:41.390
That is remote firing.

26:41.830 --> 26:44.540
Finally, I'm going to add
a camera onto the mount

26:44.750 --> 26:48.890
and a monitor under the dashboard, so
I can see exactly where I'm aiming.

26:49.290 --> 26:52.770
This camera is what turns this from
something cool into something awesome.

26:54.510 --> 26:55.570
Jamie, come here. Check it out.

26:59.620 --> 27:00.920
In your face!

27:02.640 --> 27:03.580
That looks great.

27:03.830 --> 27:08.610
Actually, I should say, it looks
like crap, but it works great.

27:09.170 --> 27:11.620
And with those words of encouragement,

27:12.240 --> 27:14.640
Adam gets on with the final
part of his firearm.

27:16.280 --> 27:19.950
A frame that should feed a plethora
of paint balls into the gun.

27:23.090 --> 27:25.630
It's not pretty, but will it work?

27:31.460 --> 27:32.240
I got you.

27:32.460 --> 27:33.820
I got you! Oh yeah!

27:34.220 --> 27:34.750
You want some of this?

27:34.920 --> 27:35.930
You want a piece of this?

27:36.120 --> 27:38.290
You want some more? Hey, do you want some?

27:40.230 --> 27:42.250
You so wish you were me right now.

27:47.240 --> 27:48.560
All right, so where do we stand?

27:48.740 --> 27:50.160
Well, we have got two issues.

27:50.360 --> 27:52.960
One, we can't get a spin from a direct hit.

27:53.050 --> 27:55.180
And two, we can't find the ricochet.

27:55.420 --> 27:57.700
Not only that. This is supposed to be easy.

27:57.800 --> 28:00.070
I mean, in the video, the guy
shoots and gets a spinning.

28:00.270 --> 28:01.740
That's not what we found at all.

28:01.950 --> 28:02.750
Not so fast.

28:02.940 --> 28:03.800
Check this out.

28:03.990 --> 28:06.160
You are not gonna believe what we found.

28:06.370 --> 28:08.460
Now, the cameraman was going
through some of the footage.

28:09.580 --> 28:10.410
Now listen.

28:11.390 --> 28:12.310
Can you hear that?

28:15.410 --> 28:18.220
I don't know what that is, but it could
potentially be a spinning bullet.

28:18.390 --> 28:20.150
I mean, we can't see it, but we can
definitely hear something.

28:20.410 --> 28:22.470
Ok, well, that brings this myth
back from the dead.

28:22.670 --> 28:24.260
I think we should
definitely stick to our plan.

28:24.490 --> 28:25.560
And the plan being,

28:25.760 --> 28:29.450
we wait until winter and try this
again on an actual frozen lake,

28:29.660 --> 28:31.070
where we might have
a chance of this working.

28:31.460 --> 28:33.370
All right. Let's reconvene in six months.

28:35.330 --> 28:39.080
From the San Franciscan sun to
a blizzard in the Sierra Nevada,

28:39.510 --> 28:42.420
this winter the team is
going that extra mile.

28:42.850 --> 28:44.050
Save yourselves.

28:45.130 --> 28:47.340
Rumor has it, there is a lake out here.

28:48.090 --> 28:49.090
I think it's over there.

28:49.470 --> 28:52.440
This looked a little more
picturesque in the brochures.

28:53.070 --> 28:55.320
All right, so what we have
behind me is a frozen lake.

28:55.670 --> 28:57.140
I know it doesn't really look like it.

28:57.141 --> 28:58.830
It looks more like a snow field.

28:59.820 --> 29:01.420
We are at 7900 feet.

29:01.590 --> 29:03.320
The temperature is 10 degrees.

29:03.550 --> 29:06.780
This is exactly what we
need to test this myth.

29:07.370 --> 29:09.940
The only problem is we're in
the middle of a snowstorm.

29:10.510 --> 29:11.860
And I'm freezing my %$& off.

29:12.140 --> 29:14.020
- Our next myth is in the Bahamas, right?
- Yeah.

29:14.240 --> 29:17.999
Despite Tori's optimism, the temperature
of his... nether regions

29:18.000 --> 29:20.770
is certainly not the only problem.

29:21.390 --> 29:24.280
Looks like building our own
frozen lake was problematic.

29:24.470 --> 29:27.530
But compared to this, it was child's play.

29:27.930 --> 29:29.500
Here is what we are up against.

29:29.770 --> 29:32.000
Our blast shields, which
we left out overnight,

29:32.040 --> 29:34.820
are now buried under six feet of snow.

29:35.430 --> 29:38.100
Our paramedic can't get here
because the road is closed.

29:38.390 --> 29:41.800
And worst of all, the lake is
buried under three feet of snow.

29:42.130 --> 29:43.970
Which means, before we do any shooting,

29:43.980 --> 29:46.940
we've got to dig to get down to the ice.

29:47.490 --> 29:50.140
And as the weather goes
from bad to worse...

29:50.670 --> 29:53.180
I have already dug two feet
and I haven't seen ice yet.

29:53.500 --> 29:55.760
...that digging gets harder and harder.

29:56.620 --> 29:57.700
So I could keep digging it out,

29:57.701 --> 30:00.640
then mother nature just
keeps filling it back in.

30:01.550 --> 30:03.980
So Kari brings in reinforcements.

30:04.390 --> 30:06.320
Since we're digging at high altitude

30:06.321 --> 30:09.330
and fighting 40 mile an hour gusty winds,

30:09.750 --> 30:12.210
we've decided to bring in a few... helpers.

30:12.780 --> 30:16.410
Like the sheriff who lives up
here, and maybe a few others.

30:16.860 --> 30:20.410
With all hands on deck, the
team exposes enough ice

30:20.520 --> 30:22.740
before anyone gets exposure.

30:22.940 --> 30:25.070
So the good news is, if you can
call anything good news

30:25.280 --> 30:27.580
in these kinds of conditions,
we found the ice.

30:27.780 --> 30:29.030
So now we are ready to start testing.

30:29.230 --> 30:32.370
Now, remember, this myth is
about shooting a nine millimeter

30:32.560 --> 30:36.790
into a frozen lake bed and finding
the bullet spinning like a top.

30:37.120 --> 30:39.480
Seems kind of counter-intuitive to...

30:39.610 --> 30:41.380
fire into the ice that you're standing on,

30:41.570 --> 30:43.080
but, I mean, this isn't Logic Busters.

30:44.090 --> 30:46.390
We've gone to great efforts
to make this myth work,

30:46.570 --> 30:50.450
including getting high-tech hearing
devices, low-tech ear trumpets,

30:50.620 --> 30:54.150
but, as you can see by the horizontal
snow zooming past the camera,

30:54.410 --> 30:56.109
there is a huge amount of wind.

30:56.110 --> 30:58.530
And that is all we are gonna hear
in those hearing devices.

30:58.830 --> 31:01.320
So, we're going old fashioned.

31:01.520 --> 31:02.150
We're running.

31:02.350 --> 31:03.240
We're listening.

31:03.570 --> 31:07.560
But will that technique be good
enough to locate the mythical spin?

31:08.950 --> 31:12.110
All right. This is spinning ice
bullet in three, two, one...

31:13.110 --> 31:15.560
Next up, Adam unleashes the beast...

31:18.110 --> 31:21.220
...peppering Jamie with spy agent arms.

31:21.400 --> 31:23.210
I might have got hit. I'm not sure.

31:27.560 --> 31:29.520
At an abandoned military base,

31:30.600 --> 31:33.110
Adam and Jamie are about
to unleash the beast...

31:33.740 --> 31:36.690
- It is a perfect day for chasing.
- And shooting.

31:36.700 --> 31:38.119
Indeed.

31:38.120 --> 31:43.530
...as they test whether a spy car's
hood-mounted howitzer can ever be accurate.

31:43.770 --> 31:45.290
Oh, yeah. Great, baby.

31:45.530 --> 31:48.299
But first up, like all good spy scientists,

31:48.300 --> 31:49.870
they are starting with a control.

31:50.240 --> 31:51.780
As long as we are shooting between cars,

31:51.960 --> 31:53.880
we thought it would be a good
idea to start with a baseline.

31:54.070 --> 31:56.670
The most common way you see people
shoot between cars in the movie,

31:56.860 --> 32:00.349
in which during the car-chase,
the driver of the chasing car

32:00.350 --> 32:02.910
will start firing at the
person that he is chasing.

32:05.680 --> 32:07.530
In this case, I will be that driver

32:08.280 --> 32:11.310
and this will be my handy service revolver

32:11.910 --> 32:15.110
and Mr. Hyneman, well, he
will be my grizzled partner.

32:15.900 --> 32:20.580
And last but not least, police driver
Brian Fraiser will play the target.

32:20.990 --> 32:24.560
OK, this is shooting
the gun out the window.

32:24.740 --> 32:26.530
Brian, you may escape when ready.

32:29.790 --> 32:30.880
Oh, it's on.

32:34.050 --> 32:35.170
Okay.

32:35.390 --> 32:39.550
Adam will have one clip or 14
bullets to take down the target.

32:40.730 --> 32:43.200
It's hard to drive one-handed,
I'll tell you that.

32:43.400 --> 32:46.959
As Brian dodges and weaves, Jamie
keeps a tally of how many rounds

32:46.960 --> 32:48.330
Adam's let rip...

32:50.390 --> 32:52.310
...and how many have hit their target.

32:52.730 --> 32:55.910
Come on, 12.
You haven't even hit the car yet.

32:56.460 --> 32:59.930
It's fair to say that this is
a lot harder than it looks.

33:03.130 --> 33:06.490
Firing the hand-held gun out of the
car proved to be far from ideal.

33:06.700 --> 33:08.190
It was more difficult than you would think.

33:08.450 --> 33:10.410
Now, not to say that it couldn't be done,

33:10.610 --> 33:13.870
but we were not able to stop
the car or kill the driver.

33:14.400 --> 33:17.159
Which begs the question,
can the spy-inspired

33:17.160 --> 33:19.510
front-facing machine gun do any better?

33:20.940 --> 33:23.510
This test is with a machine
gun in a fixed position.

33:24.060 --> 33:25.500
What do I think is gonna happen?

33:25.501 --> 33:27.629
Well, I've actually been
saying this for years

33:27.630 --> 33:30.230
and it's the reason I always
wanted to do this test.

33:30.580 --> 33:33.080
I don't think I'm gonna be able to
be very effective in hitting Jamie.

33:33.290 --> 33:37.320
I've always thought that fixed machine guns
on the hood of a car was a stupid idea.

33:37.500 --> 33:42.300
Stupid, because as target Jamie explains,
they only fire straight ahead.

33:43.820 --> 33:46.629
Now, Adam's goal is to take
me out, and that means

33:46.630 --> 33:50.090
that he has to hit me in the head,
or he has to hit the tyre of the car.

33:50.570 --> 33:53.230
Now, given that he
has got no subtle control,

33:53.420 --> 33:55.770
it's only done by aiming the car,

33:56.680 --> 33:58.530
I think it's going to be almost impossible.

33:59.780 --> 34:01.200
All right, Mr. Hyneman,

34:01.820 --> 34:04.180
you may start whenever
you think you're ready.

34:04.580 --> 34:10.659
Okay, fixed gun in three, two, one...

34:11.449 --> 34:14.139
Like the last test,
this trial will also end

34:14.340 --> 34:15.949
when the gun runs out of ammo.

34:21.370 --> 34:22.630
Come to papa.

34:22.909 --> 34:24.449
But unlike the last test,

34:24.449 --> 34:28.510
this time, Adam has got
400 paint balls to fire.

34:28.710 --> 34:30.659
Here we go. Let's see what you got!

34:30.870 --> 34:33.550
At first, things pan out just as expected,

34:33.760 --> 34:35.850
as Adam fires miss after miss.

34:37.010 --> 34:40.429
Yet, slowly but surely, he
starts to get his eye in.

34:41.659 --> 34:43.489
I might have got hit. I'm not sure.

34:43.679 --> 34:46.770
And pretty soon, the occasional hit

34:46.960 --> 34:49.270
turns into a relentless barrage of bullets.

34:52.040 --> 34:54.360
There are bullets all over the
windshield right near me,

34:54.360 --> 34:57.560
so I'm feeling pretty shot at actually.

34:57.910 --> 34:59.990
No matter what moves Jamie makes,

35:00.240 --> 35:02.440
Adam nails him every time.

35:04.540 --> 35:05.640
Until he is out of ammo.

35:08.000 --> 35:09.700
What a horror show.

35:10.870 --> 35:13.390
I think I achieved my double "O"
status on this round.

35:13.580 --> 35:16.280
Agent Hyneman has successfully
been neutralized.

35:16.440 --> 35:18.010
Not only have I taken out the mud flap,

35:18.590 --> 35:20.359
not only have I taken out of the trunk,...

35:20.384 --> 35:21.884
I'm feeling the spray!

35:21.960 --> 35:23.649
...with extreme prejudice,

35:23.650 --> 35:26.010
I've also got a clean hit
to the back of his seat,

35:26.450 --> 35:27.720
a clean hit to his helmet...

35:27.960 --> 35:28.910
I might have got hit.

35:29.090 --> 35:29.960
I'm not sure.

35:30.150 --> 35:32.790
...and I've destroyed his windshield
and several of his side windows.

35:33.070 --> 35:34.790
Well, one hit the windshield.

35:34.990 --> 35:37.600
So, given that the gun
itself couldn't move,

35:37.810 --> 35:40.120
how did Adam end up doing so well?

35:40.300 --> 35:41.370
For the first third of the test,

35:41.371 --> 35:43.700
as I catch up with Jamie
and he is swerving,

35:43.890 --> 35:47.330
it always seems that my
bullets run over his car.

35:47.520 --> 35:49.840
And I have this epiphany,
if I smack on the brakes,

35:50.050 --> 35:51.180
the front of the car goes down,

35:51.370 --> 35:52.880
and I can actually aim that way.

35:53.070 --> 35:56.190
And it turns out I can aim plus or
minus like ten degrees that way,

35:56.380 --> 35:57.450
it's fantastic!

35:57.460 --> 36:00.230
I coupled that with
swerving back and forth.

36:00.420 --> 36:04.070
And somewhere around half way
through this test, I found my level

36:05.340 --> 36:09.620
and just started laying paint balls
into the driver's cabin of Jamie's car.

36:09.960 --> 36:12.120
It worked far better than I imagined

36:12.320 --> 36:14.860
it possibly could without
having physically tried it.

36:15.230 --> 36:18.030
Coming right up, will the
team finally spin out?

36:19.100 --> 36:20.090
It is spinning!

36:20.400 --> 36:21.980
And going in for the kill:

36:23.130 --> 36:26.280
a moveable feast for Adam's aim-able gun.

36:27.080 --> 36:28.420
Aw, the aiming is awesome!

36:34.510 --> 36:37.070
Here we are on the Caples frozen lake

36:37.360 --> 36:40.470
with winds up to 25 miles an
hour straight in your face.

36:40.690 --> 36:43.610
We got temperature lows
of about negative 30.

36:43.850 --> 36:46.670
And let me tell you, it does not
look like it's going to let up.

36:48.310 --> 36:51.930
All of which is making for some
seriously challenging testing.

36:52.720 --> 36:54.730
So given the terrible conditions,

36:55.030 --> 36:56.710
here is our plan.

36:56.770 --> 37:00.140
We positioned our gun at a 42 degree angle.

37:00.760 --> 37:04.250
We are triggering it with a string
pull, and we are going to rush in

37:04.650 --> 37:06.170
to see if we can find the bullet.

37:06.490 --> 37:10.220
And given the whiteout, I think we
are also going to montage the results.

37:10.560 --> 37:11.670
Sounds like a plan.

37:11.970 --> 37:15.630
All right, this is spinning
ice bullet in three, two, one...

37:16.800 --> 37:17.900
Run like the wind!

37:18.590 --> 37:21.860
But, unfortunately, it's
another montage of failure.

37:22.080 --> 37:25.160
Here's the bullet, but it's not spinning.

37:25.360 --> 37:26.530
Not at all.

37:26.760 --> 37:27.760
As hit...

37:29.360 --> 37:30.260
...after hit...

37:31.160 --> 37:33.080
I don't see any spinning bullet.

37:33.720 --> 37:34.960
...misses out on the spin.

37:36.030 --> 37:37.730
I can't feel my fingers.

37:37.970 --> 37:40.230
And I can't see any bullet.

37:40.420 --> 37:43.160
As the temperature dips
to 5 degrees Fahrenheit,

37:44.990 --> 37:47.610
morale is just as low.

37:47.635 --> 37:48.835
This myth sucks!

37:49.150 --> 37:51.350
But Tory wants to try one more thing.

37:52.670 --> 37:54.760
Now there is a couple of things
that we think are happening.

37:54.830 --> 37:57.079
One is, maybe the bullets
are hitting the ice

37:57.080 --> 37:58.320
and skipping off into the snow.

37:58.510 --> 38:00.160
Or maybe that the bullets
are hitting the ice

38:00.185 --> 38:02.285
and actually bouncing back into the snow.

38:02.320 --> 38:04.600
So what we are going to do
is change the target area

38:04.840 --> 38:06.630
closer to the center of our ice path,

38:06.860 --> 38:08.670
take a shot and see if
we can find the bullet

38:08.730 --> 38:11.270
and see exactly what is
happening to these things.

38:11.700 --> 38:17.360
With hypothermia a very real possibility,
it really is now or never.

38:17.560 --> 38:20.270
Will giving the bullet
room to ricochet backwards,

38:20.450 --> 38:23.290
rather than forwards, finally spin out?

38:23.490 --> 38:26.880
OK, this is spinning ice bullet
with room to bounce backwards,

38:27.380 --> 38:29.650
in three, two, one...

38:30.240 --> 38:31.130
Come on!

38:32.730 --> 38:34.460
It's spinning.

38:34.680 --> 38:35.880
It's spinning!

38:36.040 --> 38:37.190
Look at that!

38:37.450 --> 38:39.120
We got a spinning bullet!

38:40.550 --> 38:41.710
Holy crap! It worked!

38:42.340 --> 38:45.070
It's the shot that brought
this myth back from the cold.

38:46.820 --> 38:48.360
I can't believe it worked.

38:48.550 --> 38:50.840
I can't believe we got a spinning bullet.

38:51.770 --> 38:55.890
At last, after countless attempts,
they got the spin they were after.

38:56.200 --> 38:58.510
And that is just the tip of the iceberg.

38:58.990 --> 39:02.640
If we get one spinning bullet, that
was successful, let's do it again.

39:03.140 --> 39:04.920
In three, two, one...

39:07.350 --> 39:08.470
It's spinning!

39:09.870 --> 39:11.510
That's the second one in a row!

39:11.800 --> 39:13.530
And when it's three for three...

39:13.555 --> 39:14.755
It is spinning!

39:14.910 --> 39:15.950
That is continued success.

39:16.150 --> 39:18.540
We have got one after the other to spin!

39:19.160 --> 39:21.120
...you might say they are on a roll.

39:24.550 --> 39:25.880
It's spinning again!

39:26.090 --> 39:27.270
We've done this over and over.

39:27.470 --> 39:28.840
This myth is confirmed!

39:28.865 --> 39:30.009
Confirmed!

39:30.010 --> 39:32.110
I cannot believe how well this is working.

39:33.840 --> 39:35.520
We tried creating an iced

39:35.740 --> 39:38.360
lake bed that we could
shoot into back at home.

39:38.640 --> 39:40.680
But it really did take this sort

39:40.900 --> 39:43.590
of extreme weather for us
to get a spinning bullet.

39:43.800 --> 39:45.070
It was all worth it,

39:45.270 --> 39:48.670
the 70 mile an hour winds, the
10 degrees, the frozen toes, and...

39:49.840 --> 39:51.060
ah, the Grant-sickle.

39:54.000 --> 39:57.060
And with that, it's time to get warmed up.

39:57.500 --> 39:59.250
Where is that rescue party?

39:59.570 --> 40:01.260
We are the rescue party.

40:14.710 --> 40:16.860
At spy car mission control...

40:16.885 --> 40:18.085
Come to papa!

40:18.270 --> 40:22.710
...the forward facing firearm just took
out its target and then some.

40:22.780 --> 40:24.910
That worked beyond my wildest dreams.

40:25.120 --> 40:26.120
So, what's next?

40:26.640 --> 40:27.850
Now it's time to unlock what

40:28.050 --> 40:31.610
I thought was going to be the secret
potential power of this rig,

40:31.810 --> 40:34.059
which is, from inside the car,

40:34.060 --> 40:37.820
I can control an X-Y axis
wherever this gun fires,

40:38.030 --> 40:40.340
I can put paint balls
where I want to put them.

40:43.780 --> 40:45.410
Adam did pretty well with the fixed gun.

40:45.690 --> 40:49.220
And it makes sense that he should be able
to do even better with an aim-able gun.

40:49.830 --> 40:53.960
But the thing is, this adds a little bit
of multitasking that he has to do,

40:53.990 --> 40:57.600
so it might actually
have the opposite effect.

40:57.820 --> 41:03.920
Okay, aim-able gun in three, two, one...

41:04.470 --> 41:07.960
For the final time, the guys
put their pedals to the metal.

41:10.800 --> 41:12.300
Here we go!

41:13.240 --> 41:14.770
Do your best, buddy.

41:15.570 --> 41:16.560
Come on, Hyneman!

41:17.140 --> 41:18.340
You are mine!

41:18.760 --> 41:21.010
Rather than unleashing
bullets from the get go,

41:21.330 --> 41:23.550
on this one Adam bides his time...

41:23.551 --> 41:25.234
Oh, listen, Hyneman!

41:25.260 --> 41:28.210
...lining up the target,
thanks to his gun's camera,

41:28.420 --> 41:30.190
and the dashboard's monitor.

41:30.490 --> 41:31.960
I'm so on you!

41:32.400 --> 41:35.580
And only when Jamie
weaves into the cross-hairs...

41:35.605 --> 41:36.805
Weave all you want, man.

41:37.110 --> 41:38.420
I can follow you.

41:38.630 --> 41:40.670
...does Adam unleash hell.

41:41.660 --> 41:43.970
It is awesome!

41:44.070 --> 41:45.910
I totally got you.

41:45.935 --> 41:47.135
Look at that! I took out your wheel!

41:49.350 --> 41:50.940
With radar-like precision,

41:51.140 --> 41:53.640
the bullets are propelled
to do maximum damage.

41:53.665 --> 41:54.629
I'm hit!

41:54.630 --> 41:58.250
So much so, that this time,
Jamie gives up the ghost...

41:58.275 --> 41:59.475
Oh, yeah!

41:59.530 --> 42:02.900
...with Adam having
fired off just 60 rounds.

42:05.990 --> 42:09.310
So, was making my hood-mounted
machine gun aim-able more effective?

42:09.530 --> 42:13.340
I think the entire story is told
from right where I'm standing.

42:13.580 --> 42:15.960
If you look at this car after this test

42:16.160 --> 42:18.189
and compare it to what this car looked like

42:18.190 --> 42:19.310
after my fixed machine gun test

42:19.480 --> 42:23.489
when it was riddled with paint, you
can just see that this is a far more

42:23.490 --> 42:25.920
surgical and effective way
to take somebody out.

42:27.520 --> 42:28.640
Ain't that the truth?

42:28.870 --> 42:33.580
Using fewer bullets to chalk up
more kill shots, the aim-able gun

42:33.770 --> 42:36.200
is the winner of this cold war.

42:36.560 --> 42:39.940
Well, I think from all this testing, we
can conclude that a machine gun

42:40.140 --> 42:42.020
on the hood of your car equals good.

42:42.210 --> 42:45.509
As a secret agent weapon, even
the stationary machine gun was

42:45.510 --> 42:46.970
far more effective than
I thought it would be.

42:47.190 --> 42:49.510
Yeah, but their effectiveness
seems to be largely due to

42:49.511 --> 42:52.590
the sheer volume of bullets
they are able to spew out.

42:53.040 --> 42:55.170
I mean, sooner or later, they
are going to hit something.

42:55.360 --> 42:57.890
Okay, but isn't that always the
point of a machine gun?

42:57.915 --> 43:00.515
Indeed it is, <i>mon frere</i>!

